The possibility of counting the voting rates in Michoacán individually is considered
According to PREP, the difference between the first and the second place in the election of the governor is nearly 27 per cent, with 879 votes of a total of 6074 not yet counted.
The possibility of the single counting of the voting list is a reality this year in the elections in Michoacán, because according to the data issued by the programmea de Resultados Electorales Preliminares (PREP) the difference between the first and second place in the governorial elections is nearly 27 percent, with 879 votes from a total of 6074 have not been counted.
In this respect, the President of the Consejo General del Instituto Electoral de Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, reminded that last 9 November the elections office had adopted a number of rules for harmonising local rules with the reforms of the federal states in election matters.
It should be recalled that Michoacán had neither adapted his political constitution nor his voting law nor his law on election law to the reforms adopted by the Congress, so that they had not entered into force during this election round. Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel avoided its publication in the State indicator within the time limits set by the Congress with the argument, or objections to it.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) decided on the constitutional complaint submitted by the local legislative and judged the vote of the State officer on the constitutional reforms as "invalid and unlawful", since it does not have the right to "decision or a veto".
María de los Ángeles Llanderal explained in an interview the possibility of individual counting the votes that, thanks to the adoption of the directives by the Consejo General del IEM, the possibility for the local election authority to count the voting lists partially or fully.
Thus, under the following conditions, the votes contained in one or more electoral packages may be partially counted The results of the protocols do not agree; the Protocol on the counting and calculation of votes is not currently present or is not in possession of the Chairman of the Electoral Committee or there are obvious errors or amendments in the protocols.
In addition, the total counting of the fully filled electoral certificates may be made if there is a difference between the presumed winner and the one on the second place that is equal or less than a percentage, provided at the beginning of the meeting there is an explicit request from the party or coalition chairman who is the second of those candidates.
The number of votes may also take place in its entirety if, after completion of the ordinary calculation, it is found that the difference between the presumed winner and the candidate at the second place is equal or less than one percentage, provided there is an explicit request from a representative of the party whose candidate has become second. In this case, the choice packages suspended by partial counting would be excluded.
It is worth noting that the elections in Morelia are in the same situation, where, according to PREP, the difference between the first and the second place is nearly 0.16 percent, although the votes of 129 of 923 election protocols have not yet been counted.
